    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Time series at a coordinate\"\nsubtitle: \"Pull one voxel's series at a world-mm point.\"\njupyter: python3\nsidebar: cookbook\n---\n\n## Goal\n\nOpen a 4-D BOLD and extract the time series at a world-millimetre\ncoordinate — with the affine inversion, rounding, and bounds check\nbehind a named operation.\n\n## Code\n\n::: {#9c0a8afc .cell execution_count=1}\n``` {.python .cell-code}\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport sys\n\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path.cwd().parents[1] / \"src\"))\n\nimport neuroim as ni\n\nrepo = Path.cwd().parents[1] if Path.cwd().name == \"cookbook\" else Path.cwd()\nbold = ni.read_image(str(repo / \"golden_tests/fixtures/tiny_bold.nii.gz\"))\n\nxyz = bold.space.grid_to_world((4, 4, 2))     # a point known to be in-grid\nts = bold.series_at_world(xyz)                # bare ndarray, length n_timepoints\ntyped = bold.series_roi_world(xyz)            # typed result with a Receipt\n\nts.shape, type(typed).__name__, typed.provenance.method_name\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=1}\n```\n((10,), 'ROIExtractionResult', 'series_roi_world')\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n`series_at_world` is the array form; `series_roi_world` is the typed\nform that carries provenance forward.\n\n## What's guaranteed\n\n- The affine inversion and rounding happen inside the call. There is\n  no hand-written `np.linalg.inv(affine) @ [x, y, z, 1]`.\n- A coordinate that maps off-grid raises before any indexing.\n\n## What survives the file\n\n`series_roi_world` returns an `ROIExtractionResult`. Its\n`.provenance` is a `Receipt`; if you build a volume from it and\n`to_nibabel()` it, the Receipt rides the NIfTI extension (see\n[Save a derived map](save-derived-map-with-provenance.qmd)).\n\n## Trapdoors\n\n::: {#93acecd7 .cell execution_count=2}\n``` {.python .cell-code}\nbold.series_at_world((9999.0, 9999.0, 9999.0))\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-error}\n\n::: {.ansi-escaped-output}\n```{=html}\n<pre><span class=\"ansi-red-fg\">---------------------------------------------------------------------------</span>\n<span class=\"ansi-red-fg\">OutOfBoundsError</span>                          Traceback (most recent call last)\nFile <span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">~/code/pycode/neuroim-python/src/neuroim/neuro_vec.py:303</span>, in <span class=\"ansi-cyan-fg\">NeuroVec.series_at_world</span><span class=\"ansi-blue-fg\">(self, world_xyz, out_of_bounds)</span>\n<span class=\"ansi-green-fg ansi-bold\">    302</span> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(0,135,0)\">try</span>:\n<span class=\"ansi-green-fg\">--&gt; 303</span>     <span style=\"font-weight:bold;color:rgb(0,135,0)\">return</span> <span style=\"color:rgb(0,135,0)\" class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">self</span><span style=\"color:rgb(98,98,98)\" class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">.</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">series_at</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">(</span>\n<span class=\"ansi-green-fg ansi-bold\">    304</span> <span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">        </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0,135,0)\" class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">int</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">(</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">voxel</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">[</span><span style=\"color:rgb(98,98,98)\" class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">0</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">]</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">)</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">,</span>\n<span class=\"ansi-green-fg ansi-bold\">    305</span> <span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">        </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0,135,0)\" class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">int</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">(</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">voxel</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">[</span><span style=\"color:rgb(98,98,98)\" class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">1</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">]</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">)</span><span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">,</span>\n<span class=\"ansi-green-fg ansi-bold\">    306</span> <span class=\"ansi-yellow-bg\">        </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0,135,0)\" c